'''Orkun Kökçü''' ({{IPA|tr|oɾˈkun ˈcœctʃy}}; born 29 December 2000) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] whom he captains. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Club career==
===Feyenoord===
A youth product of [[FC Groningen]], where he arrived after having played for local clubs around his hometown [[Haarlem]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gouka |first1=Mikos |title=Kökcü is bij Feyenoord een debutant van een andere orde |url=https://www.destentor.nl/nederlands-voetbal/kokcu-is-bij-feyenoord-een-debutant-van-een-andere-orde~afa9cc35/ |work=De Stentor |date=10 December 2018 |language=nl}}</ref> Kökçü joined the [[Feyenoord]] youth academy in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/the-50-eredivisie-u21-stars-to-watch-2018-19-orkun-kokcu/|title=The 50 Eredivisie U21 Stars To Watch 2018/19: Orkun Kokcu|date=8 August 2018|website=Football Oranje}}</ref> He made his debut for Feyenoord at the age of 17 in a 4–0 win over [[VV Gemert]] in the first round of the [[2018–19 KNVB Cup#First Round|KNVB Cup]] on 17 September 2018, scoring Feyenoord's second goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/kokcu-geeft-visitekaartje-af-bij-feyenoord-debuut-ongelooflijk-trots|title=Kökcü geeft visitekaartje af bij Feyenoord-debuut: 'Ongelooflijk trots'|website=www.vi.nl}}</ref> He made his [[Eredivisie]] debut against [[FC Emmen]] on 9 December 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/12/09/netherlands/eredivisie/fc-emmen/feyenoord-rotterdam-nv/2794060/|title=Emmen vs. Feyenoord - 9 December 2018|website=Soccerway}}</ref> and contributed with a goal and an assist after coming on as a substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gelderlander.nl/nederlands-voetbal/17-jarige-kokcu-scoort-bij-debuut-mooier-kan-bijna-niet~a7751a15/|title=Cookies op gelderlander.nl – gelderlander.nl|website=www.gelderlander.nl}}</ref> On 10 April 2019, he extended his contract at Feyenoord until 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/kokcu-na-tekenmoment---nu-hoop-ik-op-meer---100419|title=Kökcü na tekenmoment: 'Nu hoop ik op meer'|language=nl|website=www.feyenoord.nl}}</ref> On 26 June 2020, he reached an agreement to extend his contract with Feyenoord for another two years, a deal to the end of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/principeakkoord---nieuw-contract-bindt-kokcu-tot-2025-aan-feyenoord---260620|title=Principeakkoord: nieuw contract bindt Kökcü tot 2025 aan Feyenoord|date=26 June 2020|language=nl|publisher=Feyenoord}}</ref>

Following [[Jens Toornstra]]'s departure, Feyenoord head coach [[Arne Slot]] chose Kökçü as his [[captain (association football)|club captain]] on 2 September 2022.<ref>{{cite news |title=Warming-up: Slot benieuwd waar zijn selectie staat {{!}} Kökcü nieuwe Feyenoord-captain |url=https://nos.nl/liveblog/2442978-warming-up-slot-benieuwd-waar-zijn-selectie-staat-kokcu-nieuwe-feyenoord-captain |access-date=2 September 2022 |work=NOS |date=2 September 2022 |language=nl}}</ref> With Kökçü as captain, Feyenoord went on to win the [[2022–23 Eredivisie]].<ref name="2023Champions">{{cite web |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2475118-feyenoord-verslaat-go-ahead-en-is-na-zes-jaar-weer-kampioen-van-nederland |title=Feyenoord verslaat Go Ahead en is na zes jaar weer kampioen van Nederland |trans-title=Feyenoord beats Go Ahead and is champions of the Netherlands after six years |language=Dutch |date=14 May 2023 |access-date=14 May 2023}}</ref>

===Benfica===
On 10 June 2023, Kökçü joined [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] on a five-year deal for a reported fee of €25 million, plus €5 million in variables.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2023/06/10/futebol-benfica-kokcu-reforco-2023-2024 |title=Kökcü é reforço do Benfica! |trans-title=Kökcü signs with Benfica! |publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]] |language=Portuguese |date=10 June 2023 |access-date=10 June 2023}}</ref> The sum represented a record signing for the Portuguese club and the league surpassing [[Darwin Núñez]] transfer from [[UD Almería|Almería]] to Benfica in 2020 for transfer fee of €24 million and a club record sale for Feyenoord becoming the club's biggest sale since Kökçu's former Feyenoord teammate [[Luis Sinisterra]]'s transfer to [[Leeds United]] in 2022 for a fee of €25 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/benfica/detalhe/benfica-oficializa-contratacao-de-kkc-os-detalhes-do-negocio |title=Benfica oficializa contratação de Kökçü: os detalhes do negócio |trans-title=Benfica make Kökçü's signing official: the details of the deal |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=Portuguese |date=10 June 2023 |access-date=10 June 2023 |archive-date=10 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230610171943/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/benfica/detalhe/benfica-oficializa-contratacao-de-kkc-os-detalhes-do-negocio |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Kökçü made his debut for Benfica in the [[Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]], starting in a [[2023 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|2–0]] win over [[O Clássico|rivals]] [[FC Porto]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=9 August 2023 |title=Benfica 2-0 FC Porto: A Musa que faltava a Schmidt para ganhar a Supertaça |trans-title=Benfica 2-0 FC Porto: The Musa that Schmidt lacked to win the Supercup |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/supertaca/artigos/di-magia-e-inspiracao-benfica-vence-fc-porto-e-conquista-supertaca |access-date=17 September 2023 |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 2 September, netting Benfica's third goal in a 4–0 home win over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bolanarede.pt/especial-bola-na-rede/ultima-hora/kokcu-estreia-se-a-marcar-pelo-sl-benfica-com-fantastico-golo/|title=Kokçu estreia-se a marcar pelo SL Benfica com fantástico golo|publisher=Bola na Rede|language=pt|date=2 September 2023|access-date=3 September 2023}}</ref> Kökçü made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut on 20 September, starting in a 2–0 home loss to [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Delgado |first=André |date=20 September 2023 |title=Entrada em falso do Benfica na Champions face à derrota frente ao Salzburgo |trans-title=Benfica's false entry into the Champions League following the defeat against Salzburg |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/liga-dos-campeoes/artigos/entrada-em-falso-do-benfica-na-champions-face-a-derrota-frente-ao-salzburgo |access-date= |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

===Beşiktaş===
On 12 July 2025, Kökçü agreed on a loan deal with [[Süper Lig]] club [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] with an obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/oficial-kokcu-tem-novo-clube-2025071212383004451|title=Oficial: Kokçu tem novo clube|trans-title=Official: Kokçu has a new club|publisher=abola.pt|language=pt|date=12 July 2025|access-date=12 July 2025}}</ref> On 17 October 2025, Kökçü was appointed as the new captain of the team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bjk.com.tr/en/news/92653/new-besiktas-captains-revealed.html|title=New Beşiktaş captains revealed|publisher=bjk.com|language=en|date=17 October 2025|access-date=17 October 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Kökçü in the international match in March 2024 (Cropped).jpg|thumb|Kökçü playing for [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in 2024]]
Kökçü was a youth international for the Netherlands, having represented the [[Netherlands national under-18 football team|Netherlands U18]]s,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185190/speler/24446|title=OnsOranje: Jeugd mannen onder 18|website=onsoranje.nl}}</ref> and [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U19]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185189/speler/25281|title=OnsOranje: Jeugd mannen onder 19|website=onsoranje.nl}}</ref> In July 2019, Kökçü announced the intent to play for the Turkey national team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kökçü opts for Turkey over Netherlands |url=https://www.football-oranje.com/kokcu-opts-for-turkey-over-netherlands/ |website=Football Oranje |access-date=7 August 2019 |date=21 July 2019}}</ref> He represented the [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey U21]]s in a 3–2 [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] loss to the [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]]s on 6 September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/06/europe/uefa-u21-championship/turkey-under-21/england-under-21/2978844/?ICID=HP_MS_47_10|title=Turkey U21 vs. England U21 – 6 September 2019 – Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

He made his [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] debut on 6 September 2020 in a [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|Nations League]] game against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]], he started the game and played the first hour of the 0–0 away draw.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[UEFA]]|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2029998/|title=Serbia v Turkey game report|date=6 September 2020}}</ref>

In June 2021, Kökçü was included in the list of 26 Turkish players selected to compete at [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|date=4 June 2021 |language=en |title=Turkey Euro 2020 squad profile: Best player, manager and past Euros record |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/turkey-euro-2020-squad-the-complete-line-up-for-marchs-internationals |website=www.fourfourtwo.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator -->.</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was named in the final squad of 26 players chosen by [[Vincenzo Montella]] to take part in [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-06-13 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Kadrosu Açıklandı - A Milli Takım Haber Detayları TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |website=www.tff.org}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator -->.</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in the Netherlands, Kökçü is of Turkish descent,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sporx.com/hollandanin-10-numarasi-bir-turk-SXHBQ406059SXQ|title=Hollanda'nin 10 numarasi bir TURK - Futbol|last=Sporx|date=9 September 2014|website=Sporx}}</ref> from [[Suvermez, Emirdağ]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgrthaber.com/mavikadin/orkun-kokcu-kimdir-orkun-kokcu-kac-yasinda-nereli/?p=3|title=Orkun Kökçü kimdir? Orkun Kökçü kaç yaşında nereli?|date=2 July 2025}}</ref> He is the younger brother of the professional footballer [[Ozan Kökçü]] who plays internationally for the [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan national team]]. He is a lifelong fan of [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] and indicated a desire to play for the club he had been supporting since childhood.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ortacizgi.com/orkun-kokcuden-flas-besiktas-aciklamasi|title=Orkun Kökçü'den flaş Beşiktaş açıklaması! - Orta Çizgi - Beşiktaş Haberleri &#124; Beşiktaş Transfer Haberleri}}</ref>

